{
	quest.00453FF528AA0B1C.quest_desc: ["&7Lonestar Skeletons&r are hostile Mobs that can spawn anywhere. \\n\\nThey have 10 &4Hearts&r and will throw their Sword at you to attack you. \\n\\nOn death they can drop Bones, &7Deepsilver Nuggets&r, and &7Shattered Swords&r."]
	quest.00453FF528AA0B1C.title: "&7Lonestar Skeletons"
	quest.00FDBA93722ACECE.title: "&4Amaramber Hoe"
	quest.011FCC180FF3BD83.title: "&9Malarite Sword"
	quest.01F322AEFCC6109E.quest_desc: ["Tangled Skulls can be dropped from... well Tangled Skulls. \\n\\nThey can be used as a projectile like a Wither Head thrown from a Wither. \\n\\nIt will be used up when you do that though."]
	quest.02414CBEF2CD5A9D.title: "&7Deepsilver Sword"
	quest.028472D7F51D439A.title: "&aFlowglaze Scythe"
	quest.02B574B09AB45D09.quest_desc: [
		"&bFreezes&r work similar to &cBlazes&r, they'll fly up and shoot a ball at you. \\n\\nJust &bFreezes&r only throw 1 ball and it will make you cold instead of warm. \\n\\nThey have 16 &4Hearts&r and will drop &bFrozen Tubes&r on death."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_freeze.png width:150 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.02B574B09AB45D09.title: "&bFreeze"
	quest.0342248394E40B6A.quest_desc: ["This Quest has been authored by &6AllTheMods Staff&r, or a &2Community contributor&r for use in AllTheMods Modpacks.\\n\\nAs all &6AllTheMods&r packs are licensed under &eAll Rights Reserved&r, this Quest is not allowed to be used in any public packs not released by &6AllTheMods Team&r without explicit permission.\\n\\nThis quest is intentionally hidden, if you're seeing this, you're in editing mode."]
	quest.03B40AB768FC0161.quest_desc: [
		"&3Shimmer Rivers&r are friendly rivers. These won't go out of their way to kill you. \\n\\nThey sometimes connect &bSeas&r together and go through Forests. \\n\\nClearly they have &9Water&r but within the &9Water&r is plenty of goods!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_river.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.03B40AB768FC0161.title: "&3Shimmer River"
	quest.0576C32B0FB360B0.quest_desc: [
		"The &l&9Lunar Monstrosity&r has 200 &4Hearts&r and will only take 1 damage from each hit unless you use Fire. \\n\\nIt has a few attacks including Ground Spikes, Projectiles, and Exploding Tangled Heads! \\n\\nWhen you kill it, it will drop Arrows, Ingots, Tangled Skulls, &9Tenacious Petals&r, &5Tenacious Vines&r, &9Soul Dew&r, and a chance at a rare Weapon!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_lunar.png width:100 height:125 align:center}"
	]
	quest.0576C32B0FB360B0.title: "&9&lLunar Monstrosity"
	quest.061C4A9E439CE09B.title: "&9Malarite Shovel"
	quest.0688CE330DAF8714.title: "&cStarfire Hoe"
	quest.06D3EC025557855F.title: "&7Deepsilver Axe"
	quest.0720474D384F4774.quest_desc: ["&eMarimold&r are Mushrooms that grow Underwater. \\n\\nYou can find big and little versions of them. \\n\\nThe Blocks look like a mix of &6Honey&r and &eShroomlights&r. "]
	quest.0720474D384F4774.title: "&eMarimold"
	quest.0854589F28AAA8D0.title: "&dStarlit Diamond Hoe"
	quest.09981C89C585002E.title: "&bGlacite Helmet"
	quest.09C3C0F0278C842F.title: "&4Amaramber Chestplate"
	quest.0BB8D556305EB307.quest_desc: [
		"Ether River is something you'll know when you see it. \\n\\nIt's bright, very bright and might appear red in your Map, that's a bug ignore that. "
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_ether.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.0BB8D556305EB307.title: "Ether River"
	quest.0C096EE635645E43.quest_desc: ["The &dCrystal &bCrossbow&r is a crafted like a &7Mechanical &3Crossbow&r just with &bCrystals&r instead of sticks. \\n\\nIt shoots Arrows and does same damage as a normal Crossbow but this one gives Crystal Infection. Crystal Infection does 1 damage every second with the Crystals that spawn on them! And yes it will kill them."]
	quest.0C096EE635645E43.title: "&dCrystal &bCrossbow"
	quest.0CFAAF6F13EB6C2C.title: "&cStarfire Hammer"
	quest.0D1C143B2C788204.quest_desc: ["&5Seekers&r are Hostile Mobs which can Spawn anywhere in the &9&lStarlight&r. \\n\\nThey have 12 and a half &4Hearts&r and fly around. \\n\\nThey will Attack you by flying close and shooting their tongue at you. \\n\\n&5Seekers&r are also a great way of Farming &5Seeking Eyes&r!"]
	quest.0D1C143B2C788204.title: "&5Seekers"
	quest.0D427BD581ADC3A6.title: "&aFlowglaze Pickaxe"
	quest.0E1C2DA415D5742D.title: "&bGlacite Sword"
	quest.0F0D41F29386333A.quest_desc: ["&dScarlet Trees&r range in size and shape and even sometimes fallen down! \\n\\nBut all have &dpink Leaves&r! Including the ones on the ground."]
	quest.0F0D41F29386333A.title: "&dScarlet Trees"
	quest.0F4783FA019C4567.quest_desc: ["&4Amaramber&r is found rarely by stripping &cTorreya Logs&r. \\n\\nIt can be crafted into Ingots to make Armor and Tools or used in other recipes like a campfire which will you give you regen!"]
	quest.0F4783FA019C4567.title: "&4Amaramber"
	quest.0F812AE4F247FF1C.title: "&bGlacite Chestplate"
	quest.0F8955B74DBDF5F9.title: "&cStarfire Scythe"
	quest.0FE15701F2EDC3E9.quest_desc: ["By stacking an &5Aethersent Block&r with a &5Lunaris Cactus Fruit&r we can make an &5Aethersent Golem&r! \\n\\nThis bad boy has one job, prevent &5Creteor&r Spawns from &5Meteor Showers&r. \\n\\nIf a &5Meteor Shower&r happens, he'll shoot them down before they can even Spawn! "]
	quest.0FE15701F2EDC3E9.title: "&5Aethersent Golem"
	quest.10AB188AC6FB24D3.quest_desc: [
		"The &b&lStarlight Golem&r has 220 &4Hearts&r and 2 Modes. \\n\\n1st mode is his attack mode, here he can't be damaged instead you'll have to wait for his attacks to go before hitting him. He attacks with Fireballs, Ground Pound, or a devastating Laser Beam! \\n\\nHis 2nd mode is his charging mode; in this one he'll begin taking power from the Energy Blocks which will need to be turned off in order to damage him. \\n\\nOn death he will drop plenty of Ingots and Arrows, &bGolem Steel&r, Forge Armor Trim, and maybe even the Energy Sword!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_golem.png width:150 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.10AB188AC6FB24D3.title: "&b&lStarlight Golem"
	quest.10D78DC368E16987.title: "&aFlowglaze Axe"
	quest.11783E5EF07481C3.title: "&aFlowglaze Bow"
	quest.127D085D6C9DB690.quest_desc: ["&eSaltpeter&r can be found anywhere Underground but very common in the &dWarm Shore&r Biome. \\n\\nIt needs a Stone Pickaxe to mine it and when mined it will drop a couple &eSaltpeter Powder&r. Yes, Fortune works on it! \\n\\nThe &ePowder&r can be used as a replacement for other Niters."]
	quest.127D085D6C9DB690.title: "&eSaltpeter Powder"
	quest.144ECED643031A9A.quest_desc: ["Glowing Mushrooms are huge Mushroom plants you can find in the Scarlet Forests! \\n\\nThey function just like Brown or Red Mushrooms just these ones Glow much brighter! \\n\\n(If you didn't know Brown and Red Mushrooms actually emit a Light Source level of 1)."]
	quest.15195F456D8AD4C8.quest_desc: ["When Ether touches &9Water&r, &aThioquartz&r will form. This can happen naturally with random generation or you can make it happen! \\n\\nThese aren't how we get Shards though, those are from &aBudding Thioquartz&r!"]
	quest.15195F456D8AD4C8.title: "&aThioquartz"
	quest.1533D98B3B2A758E.quest_desc: ["&7Shattered Swords&r can either be dropped from &7Lonestar Skeletons&r or crafted using the dropped &7Blades&r. \\n\\nThe &7Shattered Sword&r is used more like a Trident than a Sword, instead of hitting you'll throw it. Then, you can Right Click to bring back the &7Blade&r like a Loyalty Trident, and Right Click again to reload it if needed."]
	quest.1533D98B3B2A758E.title: "&7Shattered Sword"
	quest.17A8E4151DE37015.quest_desc: ["In order to make the &cStarfire&r Tools and Weapons you'll first need &6Thermal Springstone&r Tools to upgrade. Then, the &cUpgrade Template&r. \\n\\nThe &cStarfire Upgrade Template&r is found in the Boss Structures: &9Cursed Garden&r and &bGolem Forge&r."]
	quest.17A8E4151DE37015.title: "&cStarfire Template"
	quest.17D82EEA20D02EC8.quest_desc: ["Lining the &bSea&r floor is &5Dusted Gravel&r. \\n\\nIt can be used as a replacement for normal &7Gravel&r and can rarely drop &5Dusted Shards&r which can make other Blocks!"]
	quest.17D82EEA20D02EC8.title: "&5Dusted Gravel"
	quest.17EC65B33AC5F0B4.quest_desc: [
		"&8Thirst Walkers&r are neutral Mobs that spawn on the surface of the &5Crystallized Deserts&r. \\n\\nWhen aggro-ed they will hit you and give you Hunger. \\n\\nThey have 20 &4Hearts&r and can drop &8Tooth of Hunger&r on death."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_thirst.png width:100 height:125 align:center}"
	]
	quest.17EC65B33AC5F0B4.title: "&8Thirst Walker"
	quest.1815A439BA9879B7.quest_desc: [
		"The &dWarm Shore&r is a pretty boring Biome and is mostly for connecting the &bStarlit Sea&r and land. \\n\\nIt has &dTwilight Sand&r with Stone beneath it. I also found, more than usual, &eSaltpeter&r here."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_shore.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.1815A439BA9879B7.title: "&dWarm Shore"
	quest.18AA0B2E9C3B912A.quest_desc: ["It's a &9Snail&r. \\n\\nIt will Drop its Shell and Meat."]
	quest.18AA0B2E9C3B912A.title: "&9Shadow Snail"
	quest.19B8871B701F11F4.title: "&dStarlit Diamond Pickaxe"
	quest.19F7BAD1150A2107.quest_desc: ["&cStarfire&r! \\n\\nNo, not like from Teen Titans or Teen Titans Go. This one is a material which can be used to make Tools and Weapons or..."]
	quest.19F7BAD1150A2107.title: "&cStarfire"
	quest.1A95BFE57029F9C4.quest_desc: ["Upset we didn't get the Tuff Golem? Well don't you fret, we have the &7Grimstone Golem&r! \\n\\nHe does the same exact thing, just stands there and holds a Block or Item. \\n\\nJust place a &5Lunaris Cactus Fruit&r over &7Grimstone Bricks&r and you'll get it."]
	quest.1A95BFE57029F9C4.title: "&7Grimstone Golem"
	quest.1AAFC306507DFCF8.title: "&bGlacite Scythe"
	quest.1AB17923F87AE264.quest_desc: [
		"The Yeti is a name that strikes fear into all those who explore the Cold! An abominable furry creature that lives in the harshest coldest climate eating anything that dare venture there! \\n\\nWell not this Yeti, these ones are cute and friendly! They'd rather roll around than eat you. \\n\\nHeck they don't even fight back and only have 10 &4Hearts&r. \\n\\nOn death they will drop their Fur and String, the former which can be used as a replacement for Wool."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_yeti.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.1AB17923F87AE264.title: "Yetis"
	quest.1AFCA421A6A50DA4.quest_desc: ["&aFlowglaze Upgrade Template&r also Spawns in Boss Structures: &9Cursed Garden&r and &bGolem Forge&r. \\n\\nYou'll need to apply the &aFlowglaze&f and &aUpgrade Template&f to &bGlacite &fto make &aFlowglaze Weapons&r."]
	quest.1AFCA421A6A50DA4.title: "&aFlowglaze Template"
	quest.1C863B4BC6EAD1CD.title: "&9Malarite Sickle"
	quest.1E7B5CDF0D5F833F.title: "&7Deepsilver Pickaxe"
	quest.1EA98CFE85035939.title: "&5Aethersent Bottoms"
	quest.1ECD4331DDFBBB52.quest_desc: ["&cTorreya Trees&r are huge purple/pink Trees that stand around 40 Blocks tall. \\n\\nThe Leaves will sprout out in every direction and the &eTorreya Vines&r hang from them."]
	quest.1ECD4331DDFBBB52.title: "&cTorreya Trees"
	quest.20D705C99BD11F18.title: "&cStarfire Axe"
	quest.252AD9C886DE45C8.quest_desc: [
		"&9Twilight Gaze&r are a neutral Fish located in &5The Abyss&r. \\n\\nIf you hit one, all will attack you, similar to Wolves or Zombified Piglins. If you get too far from &5The Abyss&r they will stop following you and swim back to the depths. \\n\\nThey don't drop anything on death so maybe don't hit them..."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_gaze.png width:150 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.252AD9C886DE45C8.title: "&9Twilight Gaze"
	quest.2583E4890619044E.title: "&6Thermal Springstone Sword"
	quest.25B45E8FBC9705B3.title: "&dStarlit Diamond Axe"
	quest.25E782DB4309A1B8.quest_desc: ["&3Aurora Deer Antlers&r are dropped by &3Aurora Deers&r on death. \\n\\nIt can be used as a Sword or a Hoe."]
	quest.25E782DB4309A1B8.title: "&3Aurora Deer Antlers"
	quest.271A112ABDD923A6.quest_desc: ["Like normal Mangrove but these aren't ugly."]
	quest.271A112ABDD923A6.title: "&9Banyin Trees"
	quest.27D8E62556F7CE8D.title: "&6Thermal Springstone Hoe"
	quest.282AEEC832FFC8D7.title: "&4Amaramber Axe"
	quest.2872C4229702B077.title: "&bGlacite Pickaxe"
	quest.29283BF1B6ED3634.quest_desc: ["The &7Mechanical &3Crossbow&r is made like a normal Crossbow just with &bGolem Steel&r. \\n\\nIt works like a normal Crossbow just much stronger! And can be enchanted to do even more!"]
	quest.29283BF1B6ED3634.title: "&7Mechanical &3Crossbow"
	quest.298963543B99734E.quest_desc: ["The &bStarlit Seas&r spawn their own versions of Coral! \\n\\nJust don't be like me and forget Silk Touch to pick them up..."]
	quest.298963543B99734E.title: "Coral Blocks"
	quest.29A1E1FF02BD9219.quest_desc: [
		"A &3Forest&r as blue as the Ocean. \\n\\nThe &3Starlight Forest&r is by far the most common biome in the &9&lStarlight&r. \\n\\nIt has dozens of &3Lunar Trees&r covering it entirely with plenty of Mobs, passive and hostile, below it."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_forest.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.29A1E1FF02BD9219.title: "&3Starlight Forest"
	quest.29EC143D7E0347DE.quest_desc: ["The &8Dagger of Hunger&r is made with the &8Teeth of Hunger&r. No, I am not saying Tooths. \\n\\nThe &8Dagger&r has a Hunger Value. When you hit Mobs it will go up, when it's inactive it will decrease. When it gets to 100% you'll get boosts. And if it goes to 0% it will start killing you. \\n\\nWhen you hit Mobs (or Players) it will also give the Hunger effect. \\n\\nI don't blame it, I get angry when hungry too."]
	quest.29EC143D7E0347DE.title: "&8Dagger of Hunger"
	quest.2A14A47E40A97329.title: "&aAlchemist Mask"
	quest.2D457E53BB6D63C7.quest_desc: [
		"Highest points in the &9&lStarlight&r is the Permafrost Forests which lie upon Mountains. \\n\\nBeing so far up makes them much colder making them covered in Snow and Ice! \\n\\nAtleast the friendly Mobs seem to enjoy the Cold!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_permafrost.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.2D457E53BB6D63C7.title: "Permafrost Forest"
	quest.2DA8CE213AC3869B.quest_desc: ["&bStarlight &dCrystals&r can be found all over and even under the &5Crystallized Deserts&r. \\n\\nThey work similar to &5Amethyst&r and even sound like it!"]
	quest.2DA8CE213AC3869B.title: "&bStarlight &dCrystals"
	quest.2E29DC243E8AD61E.quest_desc: [
		"&9Shimmer Lacewings&r don't do or drop anything, they just add atmosphere. \\n\\nThey also resemble the only bug I tolerate!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_shimmer.png width:150 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.2E29DC243E8AD61E.title: "&9Shimmer Lacewing"
	quest.2E9D3DA2DF3E3AC9.quest_desc: ["The &5Petal &bScythe&r gives Poison to all it Hits. \\n\\nJEI says it can make Farmland but in game it won't... \\n\\nWhen Hitting &9Water&r a bunch of Particles will come up. \\n\\nI don't think this Item is finished."]
	quest.2E9D3DA2DF3E3AC9.title: "&5Petal &bScythe"
	quest.2F3E7233129F2B89.quest_desc: [
		"Acts exactly like a Luminofish just these have a horn on their head!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_fish2.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.2F3E7233129F2B89.title: "Luminaris"
	quest.306A5B38B52F65F3.title: "&4Amaramber Pickaxe"
	quest.3124D945A54938C2.quest_desc: ["Swamp Silver used to Spawn in the &9Swamps&r but it has been promoted (or demoted I don't know) to Spawning everywhere and now in the &9Swamp Malarite&r will Spawn. "]
	quest.3124D945A54938C2.title: "&9Malarite"
	quest.315F1CB8158DFB92.title: "&5Aethersent Hood"
	quest.31DDEA54B6E81EEE.title: "&7Deepsilver Helmet"
	quest.337D376BE2653F0F.title: "&bGlacite Boots"
	quest.34119FC1728B75B9.title: "&4Amaramber Helmet"
	quest.342EEB042DEC2B8C.quest_desc: ["Magma and Geysers both spawn on the bottom of &5The Abyss&r. \\n\\nMagma will help you get down below and help keep your breath. \\n\\nGeysers just look cool!"]
	quest.342EEB042DEC2B8C.title: "Magma and Geysers"
	quest.34D7CA6F99B29C87.title: "&2Air Sac Mask"
	quest.362F4CFD1B8B12B1.quest_desc: ["All living things will die in Ether as if it were Lava. Funny enough you can put it in a Bucket though! \\n\\nThe only way to get it is finding it in the Ether River. \\n\\nWhen Water touches Ether it will form &aThioquartz Blocks&r!"]
	quest.36BCCF7395658A5C.quest_desc: ["The Bosses in the &9&lStarlight&r live in their structures. These aren't common (thankfully) so you might need assistance aka the Seeking Eyes. \\n\\nSeaking Eyes work like &aEnder Eyes&r, Right Click with them to throw them and follow them to get to the structures. \\n\\nTo set the structure you'll need a certain Item in your Offhand, items like..."]
	quest.36BCCF7395658A5C.title: "Finding the Bosses"
	quest.37355F60E45777FE.quest_desc: ["The &3Orb of Prophecy&r can be crafted or obtained through beating the &7&lGatekeeper&r! \\n\\nIt's main use is activating the Portal, but there will be more uses for it!"]
	quest.37355F60E45777FE.title: "&3Orb of Prophecy"
	quest.373CA701008A9584.quest_desc: ["The &4Wilted Crossbow&r needs both the &9&lLunar Monstrosity&r and &b&lStarlight Golem&r killed. \\n\\nThe &4Wilted Crossbow&r is like a normal Crossbow, just every Arrow will deal Wither and Slowness."]
	quest.373CA701008A9584.title: "&4Wilted Crossbow"
	quest.375F0A098589CF29.quest_desc: [
		"Using your Seeking Eyes you might become confused why they've suddenly gone underground. That's probably because the &bGolem Forge&r is deep underground, like in the negative Y levels. \\n\\nThere's many winding rooms each full of Loot, &cLava&f, and &bFreezes&r! The room we are looking for holds the &b&lStarlight Golem&r!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_golemforge.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.375F0A098589CF29.title: "&bGolem Forge"
	quest.378A7484CF999F03.quest_desc: ["These would be perfect for tiny underwater dollhouses! \\n\\nIf there's even a single other person in history who thought of that as an idea..."]
	quest.378A7484CF999F03.title: "&dSpiral Kelp"
	quest.37E49A1A6BA0E28D.title: "&5Aethersent Cape"
	quest.38CF9E6E7490BD50.title: "&6Thermal Springstone Hammer"
	quest.39796595B42BB41E.quest_desc: ["The &7Energy &bBoomerang&r is a unique Weapon made of &8Golem Steel&r. \\n\\nTo use it, just Right Click. This will Throw it. \\n\\nLike every other Boomerang, except for the ones I've thrown, it will return to you. It will come back after around 10 Blocks or if it Hits a Block. \\n\\nIf it Hits a Mob it will Deal Damage and set them on Fire."]
	quest.39796595B42BB41E.title: "&7Energy &bBoomerang"
	quest.3991EEEFDD263A91.quest_desc: [
		"&9Nightfall Spiders&r, like &7Lonestar Skeletons&r, are Hostile and spawn anywhere. \\n\\nThey have 5 &4Hearts&r and attack by hitting you. After hitting you they will give you the Glowing effect for a few seconds. \\n\\nOn death they will drop String and their eyes!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_spider.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.3991EEEFDD263A91.title: "&9Nightfall Spiders"
	quest.3A33514BD62CD7D9.title: "&bGlacite Axe"
	quest.3A6C912577A615EE.title: "&dStarlit Diamond Sword"
	quest.3AFEE53B4276F8CA.quest_desc: ["Finally, a Tool! \\n\\nThe &3Underminer&r is a Pickaxe. Its gimmick is that the lower your Y Level, the faster it Mines. \\n\\nHow does it know how low it is though?"]
	quest.3AFEE53B4276F8CA.title: "&3Underminer"
	quest.3BAF4078F5776809.title: "&6Thermal Springstone Chestplate"
	quest.3C37018123D3653C.title: "&2Air Sac Boots"
	quest.3C74DAE7EC844A98.quest_desc: ["The &3Lunar Berries&r are an excellent Food Source, plus very easy to get! \\n\\nThey spawn growing down from &3Lunar Tree Leaves&r, you can pluck the &3Berries&r off the Vines like &eGlow Berries&r. \\nJust these give much more Food Points and Saturation!"]
	quest.3C74DAE7EC844A98.title: "&3Lunar Berries"
	quest.3CAD0701EC16C2D8.quest_desc: [
		"&9Dark Swamps&r litter the world of the &9&lStarlight&r. \\n\\nHere you can find plenty of plants, animals, and of course Mud."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_swamp.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.3CAD0701EC16C2D8.title: "&9Dark Swamp"
	quest.3D26E7BFE0AA964A.quest_desc: [
		"The Luminofish is a glowing fish that lives within &5The Abyss&r.\\n\\nThey act just like normal Fish. You can fish for them, put them in a Bucket, you can even cook them!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_fish1.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.3D26E7BFE0AA964A.title: "Luminofish"
	quest.3D4032E7119AF8B7.quest_desc: ["&5Sonar Bombs&r are made with &9Shivering Gel&r which is dropped from &dCrystallized Moths&r. \\n\\nThey can be thrown to damage any Mob (and Player) in a huge area! It will also shake the players screen and play a loud sound effect. \\n\\nIt is disorienting so only use it on your friends!"]
	quest.3D4032E7119AF8B7.title: "&5Sonar Bomb"
	quest.3D7CEED6B974ED8C.title: "&5Aethersent Boots"
	quest.40786B63E2901D11.quest_desc: [
		"Let's see how do I describe the &9Cursed Garden&r... it's a big freakin' maze! \\n\\nThere's entrances on each side and you must find your way to the middle where the &9&lLunar Monstrosity&r is!\\n\\nAll around the maze you can find chests full of Loot and &9Tangled&r!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_maze.png width:150 height:150 align:center}"
	]
	quest.40786B63E2901D11.title: "&9Cursed Garden"
	quest.40C776497D68367F.quest_desc: ["Vines, &dRed &fand &bBlue Crystal Moss Carpets&r, &3Lunar Berries&r, Cave Moss, and &dRed &fand &bBlue Crystal Roots&r. \\n\\nThese can be used in your Offhand with the Seeking Eye to find the &9Cursed Garden&r."]
	quest.40C776497D68367F.title: "&9&lMonstrosity&r Items"
	quest.41197BEBED4A9B69.title: "&7Deepsilver Hoe"
	quest.4147D247E4D754D0.quest_desc: [
		"&7Gleeches&r are tiny little mobs that spawn in the &5Crystallized Desert&r. \\n\\nThey relentlessly want your blood and that means even through violent ways. Thankfully they only have 4 &4Hearts&r! \\n\\nOn death they might drop their &7Eggs&r which can be thrown as a projectile."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_gleech.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.4147D247E4D754D0.title: "&7Gleech"
	quest.41C70F0873E14307.quest_desc: ["There is Trees in the Desert! \\n\\nNo, wait, there was Trees..."]
	quest.41C70F0873E14307.title: "&8Dead Lunar Log"
	quest.429785E8F64929CE.quest_desc: ["In order to get to the &9&lStarlight Dimension&r you'll need to find &7Portal Ruins&r in the &2&lOverworld&r. \\n\\nThere you will find a &7&lGatekeeper&r, Right Click to initiate a conversation and challenge them to a duel! Careful, they are very tough. \\n\\nThe Gatekeeper will also deem you worthy if you have defeated the Ender Dragon, and allow you to skip the duel.\\n\\nOnce you win the duel you'll be gifted a few Items, the &3Orb of Prophecy&r being one. Right Click the &7Portal&r with the &3Orb&r to activate it! Then, walk in to get to the..."]
	quest.429785E8F64929CE.title: "The Gatekeeper and The Gate"
	quest.45AA690C89BF6845.title: "&6Thermal Springstone Leggings"
	quest.45B0442B80A7C7FB.title: "&9Malarite Axe"
	quest.45D73CA0A7BE4666.quest_desc: [
		"The &eLush Shallow Sea&r lives up to its name, it has a lot of Plant life and isn't that deep! \\n\\nIt's only around 20 Blocks deep."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_shallow.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.45D73CA0A7BE4666.title: "&eLush Shallow Sea"
	quest.46E32356964E56A0.title: "&7Deepsilver Leggings"
	quest.470EA6870DBBB352.title: "&7Deepsilver Chestplate"
	quest.474C8AF9D536D4E7.title: "&6Thermal Springstone Shovel"
	quest.47CB136D7764B86D.quest_desc: ["&eTorreya Vines&r are found hanging from &cTorreya Trees&r. \\n\\nThey are hanging because they can't be placed any other way... \\n\\nThe bulb at the bottom of them will emit Light!"]
	quest.47CB136D7764B86D.title: "&eTorreya Vines"
	quest.47DF2314B10146E9.title: "&6Thermal Springstone Pickaxe"
	quest.484ABFF266C8791E.quest_desc: ["&eOrbflora&r are plants that grow from the &bSea&r floor. \\n\\nThey can be harvested anytime but if you want the &eOrbflora Lights&r you'll need to wait! \\n\\nWhen they grow to the Sea Level they will flower. After flowering they will grow the &eLight&r!"]
	quest.484ABFF266C8791E.title: "&eOrbflora"
	quest.49D1EA8E812A12F6.quest_desc: ["It's just a neat plant. \\n\\nYou'll need a Sickle to collect it! \\n\\nI don't know why, I've never cared about plants, but Reeds are cool to me. Maybe it's the being by &9Water&r, or Cattails looking like Corndogs. I don't know but I like them."]
	quest.49DC0BD7DC1B893C.quest_desc: ["&5The Abyss&r are deep trenches within &bStarlit Seas&r. These going as far down as -50! \\n\\nThey have multiple colored layers of Stone lining them and hold many different Blocks, Mosses, and Fish!"]
	quest.49DC0BD7DC1B893C.title: "&5The Abyss"
	quest.4A54288FD22C903D.quest_desc: ["&2Velvetumoss&r spawns within &5The Abyss&r. \\n\\nYou can mine &2green&r ones to get &2Velvetumoss Balls&r which can either be eaten or made into a &aSlimeball&r! \\n\\nThe &4Red&r ones will spawn pretty plants!"]
	quest.4A54288FD22C903D.title: "&2Velvetumoss &fand &4Red &fversion"
	quest.4A5EA948F5DCEB73.quest_desc: ["&7Deepsilver&r used to be called Swamp Silver and only Spawned in &9Dark Swamps&r. \\n\\nNow it is found everywhere underground... that is probably why they changed the name!"]
	quest.4A5EA948F5DCEB73.title: "&7Deepsilver"
	quest.4B097031A3EE930B.title: "&bGlacite Hoe"
	quest.4B13835110F1FE82.title: "&7Deepsilver Sickle"
	quest.4C23D7E3DC8327C2.quest_desc: ["In order to kill the &9&lLunar Monstrosity&r you'll need to set it on Fire! \\n\\nYou can use Flint and Steel or a &eSaltpeter Matchbox&r. \\n\\nPersonally I think the &eMatchbox&r is more fitting!"]
	quest.4C23D7E3DC8327C2.title: "Burn it!"
	quest.4C72D2BB6785CC78.title: "&cStarfire Shovel"
	quest.4D0B50731FED3CEE.quest_desc: ["To get the Cresant Spear you will need to either craft it from Items dropped by the Lunar Monstrosity and the Tangled Hatred, or have it dropped from the Lunar Monstrosity. (You'll have to kill him regardless basically). \\n\\nYou can use the Spear like a Trident and just smack Mobs or you can hold Right Click to be sent flying forward with it. If you hit any Mobs with the second attack, any Mobs nearby will also take damage."]
	quest.4D0B50731FED3CEE.title: "&bCrescent &5Spear"
	quest.4D4DE266A2A325B0.quest_desc: ["&4Redstone&r, &bGolem Steel&r, and &8Oxidized Golem Steel&r are Items used for finding the &bGolem Forge&r. \\n\\nHold one of these (most likely &4Redstone&r which does spawn in the &9&lStarlight&r underground) in your Offhand and use the Seeking Eye to find the &bGolem Forge&r which btw is underground!"]
	quest.4D4DE266A2A325B0.title: "&l&bGolem&r Items"
	quest.4D53D9BBD8279282.quest_desc: ["&3Lunar Trees&r can range from massive towering &3Trees&r, to itty bitty ones. They adapt to take as much room as they can! (That would explain &3Dense Forests&r). \\n\\nThey plant like normal Saplings and can have &3Lunar Berries&r spawn from their leaves!"]
	quest.4D53D9BBD8279282.title: "&3Lunar Trees"
	quest.4D8C9960BB675221.quest_desc: ["It has a funny name!"]
	quest.4DBC3B4D38CC6152.quest_desc: [
		"&dCrystallized Moths&r spawn deep below the &5Crystallized Deserts&r. \\n\\nThey are neutral and I recommend not hitting them because they do a ton of damage! \\n\\nThey also have 10 &4Hearts&r and can drop &bStarlight &dCrystals&r or &9Shivering Gel&r on death. \\n\\nThese pretty guys and gals can be Tamed by Feeding them Meat! Then they will Fight for you."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_moth.png width:125 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.4DBC3B4D38CC6152.title: "&dCrystallized Moth"
	quest.5003365C2A7B4B53.title: "&cStarfire Sword"
	quest.50674FE3C6BE9990.quest_desc: [
		"Just like the normal &3Starlight Forest&r just with much less spacing within Trees!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_dense.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.50674FE3C6BE9990.title: "&3Dense Starlight Forest"
	quest.50EC8F8CD04D9598.title: "&5Rage of Stars"
	quest.516AC1F0E0BCAE55.quest_desc: ["&bFrozen Tubes&r are dropped from &bFreezes&r in the &bGolem Forge&r. \\n\\nThey can be thrown like Potions to hurt whoever it hits."]
	quest.516AC1F0E0BCAE55.title: "&bFrozen Tubes"
	quest.51B1AF28328FFBAD.quest_desc: [
		"The &cSpiral Kelp Forest&r is a very disappointing Biome for Wood enthusiasts. \\n\\nThis Biomes not a Forest, it is an Ocean! And not even the Ocean Biome with a Tree, that would be the &eLush Shallow Sea&r. \\n\\nI'm sorry."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_spiral.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.51B1AF28328FFBAD.title: "&cSpiral Kelp Forest"
	quest.51B6D203E28D92BE.quest_desc: ["Hate waiting for &5Meteor Showers&r? Why not start one yourself! \\n\\nThe &5Aetherstrike Rocket&r will act like a normal Firework. Flies into the air, gives a pretty show, just this one also summons a &5Meteor Shower&r. \\n\\nYep, it will start a &5Meteor Shower&r where it was fired from. \\n\\nIt does have a Cooldown though."]
	quest.51B6D203E28D92BE.title: "&5Aetherstrike Rocket"
	quest.5244B2D6B5FA0487.quest_desc: [
		"&5Crystallized Desert&r looks like a normal Desert but shaded &5Purple&r. \\n\\nAlso with added giant crystals, I don't think normal Deserts have that..."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_desert.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.5244B2D6B5FA0487.title: "&5Crystallized Desert"
	quest.5282190D0C0C2AA9.quest_desc: ["&dStarlit Diamonds&r Spawn far Underground everywhere in the &9&lStarlight&r. \\n\\nAround Voidstone is where you'll find it. \\nJudging by the Diamond in the name, yeah it is very good for Tools and Weapons."]
	quest.5282190D0C0C2AA9.title: "&dStarlit Diamond"
	quest.53149C516E544FE9.quest_desc: ["&5Creteors&r and &5Mini Creteors&r can come from &5Meteor Showers&r. \\n\\n&5Creteors&r are Neutral, you'll need to Hit them first. They have 8 &4Hearts&r. \\n\\nWhen Hit they will roll at you and start flashing. They will Hit you for a little bit of Damage, but they will also explode! The explosion takes awhile to happen so you get time to run but when they do they will Spawn... \\n\\n&5Mini Creteors&r! These guys are much less friendly then their bigger counterparts. \\n\\n&5Mini Creteors&r will fly at you and explode. These guys only have 2 and a half &4Hearts&r. \\n\\nWhen Killed (not by exploding) both will Drop &5Aethersent&r and &5Creteor Hide&r."]
	quest.53149C516E544FE9.quest_subtitle: "Mobs from out of space? Aliens?"
	quest.53149C516E544FE9.title: "&5Creteors"
	quest.5424A0E1292B13EE.quest_desc: ["Around the &9&lStarlight&r you might find Hot Ponds. \\n\\n(These aren't a biome or structure so you'll need to just look around to find them!) \\n\\nWithin them you can find &6Thermal Springstone&r."]
	quest.5424A0E1292B13EE.title: "&6Thermal Springstone"
	quest.5466CB622A637DCD.quest_desc: ["Abyssal Fruit technically can spawn in any body of &9Water&r but its the only one that lives within the &3Shimmer Rivers&r. \\n\\nIt grows like &2Kelp&r from the floor up, but also works like &eGlowberries&r as in Fruit grows and can be collected from it."]
	quest.54DE8AAAE2181F18.quest_desc: ["The &dMoonring Greatsword&r no longer needs Drops from both Bosses, now it only needs you to Kill the &9&lLunar Monstrosity&r. \\n\\nIt works like a normal Sword, just before 1.9. It can block attacks like a shield, but it can't be spammed for full damage."]
	quest.54DE8AAAE2181F18.title: "&dMoonring Greatsword"
	quest.562B280928897E0D.title: "&dStarlit Diamond Boots"
	quest.564F0343B1704CE8.title: "&cStarfire Crossbow"
	quest.5671D301C5264C7F.title: "&cStarfire Pickaxe"
	quest.59613CCE59689263.quest_desc: ["&2Rookfish&r are cute Chess-piece-shaped Squids who Swim around in the &9&lStarlight&r. \\nThey have 5 &4Hearts&r and will Drop themselves and their Airsacs on death."]
	quest.59613CCE59689263.title: "&2Rookfish"
	quest.5B737000D540ED48.title: "&4Amaramber Sickle"
	quest.5C11E99FF201C3F9.quest_desc: ["The &8Golem Steel Greatsword&r is a very fun Weapon. \\n\\nFirst, it can Block. Just Right Click to Block. \\n\\nSecond, &bLIGHTNING BALLS&r! Whenever you Left Click 3 &bLightning Balls&r will be sent out of the &8Sword&r. &bLightning&r will connect between all 3 and will Damage anything they touch. They also bounce off Blocks. \\n\\nPlus, it's just a great &8Sword&r regardless!"]
	quest.5C11E99FF201C3F9.title: "&8Golem Steel Greatsword"
	quest.5D8E715CCB7ACCAC.title: "&dStarlit Diamond Leggings"
	quest.5DFE3CB5B0130A7A.quest_desc: ["There's plenty of plant life on top of the &3Shimmer River&r, some you can stand on!"]
	quest.5DFE3CB5B0130A7A.title: "River life"
	quest.5E8A1D47CF3C7ACF.title: "&aFlowglaze Shovel"
	quest.60FDCA2FDFE74056.quest_desc: [
		"IT'S &dPINK&r! \\n\\nHere you will find &dScarlet Trees&r with their dropped leaves piled below them. You can also find Glowing Mushrooms here!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_scarlet.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.60FDCA2FDFE74056.title: "&dScarlet Forest"
	quest.61E11E4C358898D6.title: "&dStarlit Diamond Helmet"
	quest.62A11EEC976DA5C5.title: "&aAlchemist Robe"
	quest.62B44B688D09C939.quest_desc: ["&aFlowglaze&r! \\n\\nBy Rightclicking with &cStarfire&r in hand it will throw it. This can Effect Mobs with &cStarfire&r, or if it Hits Sand it will change the Sand into &aRaw Flowglaze&r. \\n\\nJust Smelt the &aFlowglaze&r and we can use that with the Upgrade Template to make Weapons and Tools."]
	quest.62B44B688D09C939.title: "&aFlowglaze"
	quest.62DA302CF53B7C39.title: "&6Thermal Springstone Boots"
	quest.62F33BBE7BDFE404.quest_desc: ["&5Wand of &bTeleportation&r is another drop from the &9Lunar Monstrosity&r, and only that! \\n\\nYou can hold Right Click with the Wand to start it, then when you release it will teleport you to the Block you were looking at last! \\n\\nThere is a range but it's pretty far. And there is a cooldown after use!"]
	quest.62F33BBE7BDFE404.title: "&5Wand of &7Teleportation"
	quest.6314B892B569A0A5.quest_desc: ["The &9&lStarlight&r! \\n\\nA Dimension where it is constantly &9Dusk&r, and no you can't change that. \\n\\nThere is dozens of Biomes, Mobs, Bosses, and even just Blocks to find! Can you discover them all?"]
	quest.6314B892B569A0A5.title: "&9&lEternal Starlight"
	quest.63362CC33B39C627.quest_desc: [
		"Starlit Seas are huge bodies of Water sitting neatly between the Warm Shores and land. \\n\\nThey hold many wonders within them and growing in them! \\n\\nHope you brought your goggles!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_starlitsea.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.63362CC33B39C627.title: "&bStarlit Sea"
	quest.636848ED1115A0B3.quest_desc: [
		"&8Ratlins&r are peaceful Mobs that can spawn on the Surface. \\n\\nOn death they will drop Ratlin Meat, Leather, and Cave Moss. \\n\\nThe latter which can be used to Breed them together!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_rat.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.636848ED1115A0B3.title: "&8Ratlins"
	quest.641C74BFA03BC01F.title: "&bGlacite Shield"
	quest.645380EA38544D3B.title: "&bGlacite Shovel"
	quest.64B6E1ABD471CF29.title: "&7Deepsilver Boots"
	quest.66536AAF9E98C3A6.title: "&9Malarite Hoe"
	quest.66DE7EF4AFCE4F7A.title: "&7Deepsilver Shovel"
	quest.687C51D915339086.title: "&aFlowglaze Shield"
	quest.68B2D3B985FC1378.quest_desc: [
		"A bright and beautiful Forest, full of &cTorreya Trees&r and &eVines&r."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_torreya.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.68B2D3B985FC1378.title: "&cTorreya Forest"
	quest.699C6DDE6B2D51C1.quest_desc: ["&2Jinglestem Trees&r grow underwater... I wonder if there's any Trees like that in real life? \\n\\nThey have &2Algaeleaves&r, instead of normal Leaves."]
	quest.699C6DDE6B2D51C1.title: "&2Jinglestem Trees&f?"
	quest.6B00D5DBB3552F15.quest_desc: [
		"&9Tangled&r are enemies that spawn within the &9Cursed Garden&r. \\n\\nThey have 10 &4Hearts&r and will attack by smacking you. If you get hit, you'll get a small amount of Poison. \\n\\nOn death they will drop Vines and Bones but also will spawn a Tangled Skull! \\n\\nTangled Skulls act similar to Vexes, they will fly around through blocks and hit you. They only have 5 &4Hearts&r and on death will give you them as an Item."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_tangled.png width:150 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.6B00D5DBB3552F15.title: "&9Tangled"
	quest.6DCC11671A2BAA1C.quest_desc: ["Rarely in the Forests of the &9&lStarlight&r you can come across &cBirds&r. \\nIf you Feed 2 &cBirds&r some Seeds near a Nest, they'll change from &cBirds&r to love birds. \\n\\nNot really, but they'll both cuddle in their Nest. After that they will leave you a gift. Sometimes that gift will be..."]
	quest.6DCC11671A2BAA1C.title: "The birds and the... birds?"
	quest.6E970CF05B96EB20.quest_desc: ["In order to damage the &b&lGolem&r you'll need to turn off his power supply! \\n\\nTo do so you'll need to Right Click the Energy Blocks when they turn blue. \\n\\nYou can usually find 2 in the corners of the boss room and 2 above him!"]
	quest.6E970CF05B96EB20.title: "Powering down"
	quest.6EC289857CDC4969.quest_desc: [
		"&bEnts&r are another peaceful Mob spawning on the Surface of the &9&lStarlight&r. These spawning in the forests! \\n\\nThese little trees can drop Sticks, &3Lunar Berries&r, and &3Lunar Leaves&r on death. \\n\\nYou can use &3Lunar Berries&r to Breed them!"
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_ent.png width:100 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.6EC289857CDC4969.title: "&bEnts"
	quest.6ECDD55D55D4D44E.title: "&5Starfall Longbow"
	quest.6F5F6BAB09CB4F5E.title: "&9Malarite Spear"
	quest.70A82A5D17D558FB.quest_desc: ["The &bEnergy Sword&r can only be dropped from the &b&lStarlight Golem&r. \\n\\nIt works like a normal Sword but with Right Click you can dash at them while swinging it, like Genji from Overwatch! "]
	quest.70A82A5D17D558FB.title: "&bEnergy Sword"
	quest.70F8A8D6C442F2B6.title: "&aFlowglaze Hoe"
	quest.713548E540B18E07.quest_desc: ["The &9Moonring Bow&r can only drop from the &9&lLunar Monstrosity&r. \\n\\nIt shoots Arrows like a normal Bow but Ground Spikes will come the same direction the Arrow went!"]
	quest.713548E540B18E07.title: "&9Moonring Bow"
	quest.713EF442D59501BA.quest_desc: ["The &5Chain of &9Souls&r can be crafted from drops by &9&lLunar Monstrosity&r. \\n\\nIt's a grappling hook! Tap Right Click to send it and once it hits something it will start reeling you in. Then, you have to Right Click again to detach it."]
	quest.713EF442D59501BA.title: "&5Chain of &9Souls"
	quest.71C58666D4BC2508.quest_desc: ["Works like Flint and Steel!"]
	quest.71C58666D4BC2508.title: "&eSaltpeter Matchbox"
	quest.7322332BB6CF5CF7.title: "&7Deepsilver Brush"
	quest.7618153D6613790E.title: "&6Thermal Springstone Scythe"
	quest.76BFC5815FC6565C.quest_desc: ["Rarely above ground in the &9&lStarlight&r a &5Meteor Shower&r may occur. \\n\\nWhile chunks of Meteors striking the ground just feet away from you in real life it is terrifying, in &2&lMinecraft&r it is helpful! \\n\\nWhen these happen a Material called &5Aethersent&r will Spawn on the ground where Meteors hit. As well as some Mobs might Spawn from those same Meteors!"]
	quest.76BFC5815FC6565C.title: "&5Meteor Shower"
	quest.770C0975CA61CE46.quest_desc: ["&bGlacite&r can be found deep underground in the Permafrost Forests. \\n\\nIt can be used to craft Armor and Tools which help against Freezing damage!"]
	quest.770C0975CA61CE46.title: "&bGlacite"
	quest.7798BC7C5112D6FB.title: "&bGlacite Leggings"
	quest.78D26411B482CD5A.title: "&dStarlit Diamond Shovel"
	quest.79B03F769746784A.title: "&9Malarite Pickaxe"
	quest.79B33E4691E6CB45.title: "&aFlowglaze Sword"
	quest.7A16D2EB63359294.quest_desc: [
		"&3Aurora Deers&r are friendly hooved animals who also live in the cold. \\n\\nThese &3Deers&r won't try to harm you but if you get in their way when you run you might feel some &3Antlers&r. \\n\\n&3Antlers&r which can also be dropped by them on death which can be used as either a weapon or a hoe! \\n\\nThey might also drop Leather or Aurora Deer Steak."
		"{image:atm:textures/questpics/eternal/starlight_deer.png width:200 height:100 align:center}"
	]
	quest.7A16D2EB63359294.title: "&3Aurora Deer"
	quest.7AF8567CF8C543F7.title: "&6Thermal Springstone Axe"
	quest.7B5D34650BBD97D9.quest_desc: ["&5Aethersent&r is Dropped from &5Creteors&r and from &5Meteor Showers&r. \\n\\nMost &5Meteor Showers&r Drop a ton of them so don't worry!"]
	quest.7B5D34650BBD97D9.title: "&5Aethersent"
	quest.7B937E68FEFBBA98.title: "&dStarlit Diamond Chestplate"
	quest.7C53F52992EA2064.title: "&4Amaramber Shovel"
	quest.7D68FD0637351E02.title: "&6Thermal Springstone Helmet"
	quest.7D7BD1458CF12021.quest_desc: ["It is a Desert of course there's &5Cacti&r! \\n\\nThe &5Cacti&r when fully grown can grow Fruit on top of them!"]
	quest.7D7BD1458CF12021.title: "&5Lunaris Cactus"
	quest.7E90138B0A2C3210.quest_desc: ["The Northland Trees are big sturdy Trees up in the Permafrost Forests. \\n\\nThey look like Spruce but much lighter! Maybe they're an albino Spruce. \\n\\nTheir saplings need to be placed on Dirt, not Grass, and in a 2x2 formation."]
	quest.7FBB431AC055FE93.quest_desc: ["The &7Soulit Spectator&r is crafted with a &9Soul Dew&r and a &9Nightfal Spider Eye&r. \\n\\nIt works similar to a Sticky Camera from Tom Clancy's Splinter Cell. You can Right Click to send the &7Spectator&r and after a bit you will be able to see out of it. You can even see yourself with it! \\n\\nIt can't be ended early so careful when you use it. It also has durability and a cooldown."]
	quest.7FBB431AC055FE93.title: "&7Soulit Spectator"
	quest.7FBD51663C1A711A.title: "&4Amaramber Sword"
	quest.7FF77463F2A0E210.quest_desc: ["Nightfall Mud can only be found within the &9Dark Swamps&r. \\n\\nYou can make more Blocks out of it!"]
